Package: MPCurver
Type: Package
Title: Fit and Explore MPCurve Trajectory Models in R
Version: 0.2.1
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Ziang", "Zhang",
      email = "aguero.zhang@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: Implements the MPCurve statistical model for trajectory and
    pseudotime inference via Gaussian mixture models with Gaussian Markov
    random field priors on smooth latent trajectories. Provides a
    mean-field coordinate-ascent variational backend ('cavi') that is the
    recommended public workflow. Older MAP/EM backends ('csmooth_em' and
    'smooth_em') remain in the codebase but are not part of the public
    API or public website. Also includes a unified 'fit_mpcurve()'
    interface, multi-ordering partition tools via 'intrinsic_dim', and
    multiple initialization methods for the CAVI path.
URL: https://aguerozz.github.io/MPCurver/,
    https://github.com/AgueroZZ/MPCurver
BugReports: https://github.com/AgueroZZ/MPCurver/issues
